Privacy Policy
Last Updated: June 24, 2024

This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use the Sara OBAT app. It also explains your privacy rights and how the law safeguards your information.

By using the app, you agree to the collection and use of your data as described in this policy. This document was prepared with the assistance of a Privacy Policy Generator and has been adapted for our specific use.

Interpretation and Definitions
Interpretation
Words with capitalized first letters have defined meanings described below. These definitions apply whether the terms appear in singular or plural.

Definitions

Account: A unique account created for you to access our Service or parts of it.

Affiliate: Any organization that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with us.

Application: The mobile application named Sara OBAT, developed by Northeastern University, Boston Medical Center, and Tufts Medical Center.

Company: Referred to as "the Company", "We", "Us", or "Our" in this policy, refers to Northeastern University, located at 360 Huntington Ave, Boston.

Country: Refers to Massachusetts, United States.

Device: Any electronic device that can access the Service, such as a smartphone or tablet.

Personal Data: Any information that can identify an individual.

Service: Refers to the Sara OBAT mobile application.

Service Provider: A third party who processes data on behalf of the Company.

Usage Data: Data collected automatically during use of the Service (e.g., time spent viewing content).

You: The individual using the Service or the organization on whose behalf the individual uses the Service.

Collecting and Using Your Personal Data
Types of Data Collected

Personal Data
We may collect the following personal information:

First and last name

Phone number

Usage Data
We automatically collect information when you use the app, such as:

Device IP address

Browser type and version

App usage statistics

Time and date of visits

Mobile device type and identifiers

Diagnostic data

This information may also be collected when using the app on mobile devices.

How We Use Your Personal Data
We may use your data for the following purposes:

To provide and improve the Service

To manage your Account and registration

To contact you (e.g., via email, phone, or push notifications) about updates or relevant information

To respond to your requests or support needs

For research and analysis, including evaluating effectiveness and user engagement

For additional purposes, such as improving app functionality and conducting internal research

We may share your data in the following scenarios:

With Affiliates: Including institutions involved in this research project, under strict confidentiality.

With Auditors or Oversight Committees: Authorized individuals (e.g., Institutional Review Board members) may access data to ensure proper conduct of the research.

With Business Partners: For offering relevant services or resources, if applicable.

With Other Users: If you choose to share data in public areas of the app.

With Your Consent: For any other purpose you explicitly approve.

Data Retention
We retain personal data only as long as necessary for research, compliance, or legal purposes.

Usage Data is retained for internal analysis, app improvement, and legal obligations.

De-identified information may be used in future research without additional consent.

Data Transfers
Your information may be processed and stored outside your local jurisdiction. By using the app, you agree to the transfer and storage of data in accordance with this policy. All data is handled securely and in compliance with applicable laws.

Disclosure of Personal Data
We may disclose your data:

In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset transfer

When required by law or public authorities

To protect rights, safety, or prevent fraud

Data Security
We prioritize your privacy and take reasonable steps to protect your information. However, no online system is 100% secure. While we use industry-standard safeguards, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Childrenâ€™s Privacy
The Sara OBAT app is not intended for users under 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe your child has provided us with data, please contact us so we can remove it.

Third-Party Links
Our app may include links to external websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of third-party sites. Please review their privacy policies before interacting with them.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page and, when appropriate, communicated via email or app notifications. We encourage you to review this policy regularly.

